task.summary: Substantially updated documentation. Split user and developer notes into USER_HOW-TO.txt and README.txt.
Bug fixes to make basin splitting and model running work for 12h STCR versions. Updated analysis codes to compare any two model runs instead of just manual vs. auto.
Compare_hydrographs.py and getFlowData.py updated to accommodate up to five model versions to plot on same figure. Compare_Config.py was also updated to use only one list of versions.
Compare_StorageOutflow.py and getSOData.py updated to accommodate up to five model versions to plot on same figure.
Compare_peakTimeElev.py and getPeakData.py updated to accommodate up to five model versions to plot on same figure.
Added output of reservoir storage for each subbasin in createStorageOutflowCurves.py and copyStorageOutflowCurves.py.
Added feature that allows a different release rate for a specified list of subbasins (InitHMS.py).

Added Compare_Inundation.py, which optionally calls HEC_Inundation.py, calculates the difference between a base model version and up to four other model versions, and plots the differences in depth vs. time step on a scatter plot. Also updated HEC_Inundation.py to be imported into another python script.
Updated createStorageOutflowCurves.py to add a (0,0) point to the beginning of all rating curves and add 0.00001 to all subsequent outflow values to make the second outflow point larger than 0.
Updated documentation.
Added makeMaxWselCsv.py to create a CSV file for Ryan Meekma's map of max depth changes.
Documentation updates. Cleaned up unneeded code. Added difference calculation to makeMaxWselCsv.py.
Updated hydrograph plots to look nicer. Added script to calculate the max reservoir storage required in the model.
